OL,6,FWhen questioned about reports that
OL,7,Fsmoking in outdoor restaurants, areas
OL,8,Foutside nightclubs and pavements by
OL,9,Funiversities and hospitals could be
OL,10,Fbanned, the Prime Minister said: "My
OL,11,Fstarting point on this is to remind
OL,12,Feverybody that over 80,000 people lose
OL,13,Ftheir lives every year because of
OL,14,Fsmoking.
OL,16,F"That is a preventable death, it's a
OL,17,Fhuge burden on the NHS and, of course,
OL,18,Fit is a burden on the taxpayer.
